1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:50,710
[Previously]
Do you really think I don’t know who she is?

25
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:53,509
I’d known it since the very first day I met your sister.

26
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:54,910
You used my sister.

27
00:01:54,930 --> 00:01:56,680
You’ve never loved her all this time, haven’t you?

28
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:59,050
Well, it’s just a game. Don’t take it personal.

29
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:00,710
You heard everything, right, Lada?

30
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:03,400
Lada.

31
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:07,080
I’m so stupid. I should’ve listened to you

32
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:11,310
Fah sent us an SOS saying that you’re in need of help.

33
00:02:12,330 --> 00:02:13,310
Give me a hug.

34
00:02:13,730 --> 00:02:15,510
It’s all right.

35
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,850
Don’t go anywhere tomorrow.

36
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:22,180
Dad has invited Mr. Huad and Kirk for dinner at our place.

37
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,450
And don’t do anything that might embarrass Dad again.

38
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,510
Understood.

39
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,079
If you come to our place, you must try the fish.

40
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,110
It surely looks tempting.

41
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:40,480
Wow, awesome!

42
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:46,250
If you don’t like anything, feel free to comment. I’ll give your feedback to our chef.

43
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:49,180
Oh, I wouldn’t dare.

44
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:52,710
Oh, I wouldn’t dare. Isn’t he a five-star hotel chef?

45
00:02:52,730 --> 00:02:54,610
It doesn’t matter how many stars he’s got.

46
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:57,150
If anyone in my family says i

47
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,650
t’s not good, then it’s not.

48
00:02:58,650 --> 00:03:00,980
The chef must listen and try to improve.

49
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:06,310
I really like it when you call us ‘family’.

50
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:08,480
It makes my heart feel so warm.

51
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:18,550
But if you want my comment, maybe you should take better care of my future daughter-in-law.

52
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:23,010
She looks a bit too thin.

53
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:27,079
Will she be able to give me a grandson as her firstborn?

54
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:30,510
Of course, you’ll surely get that.

55
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:37,950
Lada, what Zodiac year you said you were born in?

56
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,180
Year of the Tiger.

57
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,550
Tiger?

58
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:49,880
A girl born in the Tiger year isn’t quite a good match for Kirk.

59
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:54,550
With such a strong fate, she’d only make her husband feel inferior.

60
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,950
I don’t think so.

61
00:03:59,329 --> 00:04:03,050
Lada was born early in the year.

62
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:07,080
If we count it the Chinese way, it was actually a golden year.

63
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,510
- Really?
- Yes.

64
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:11,730
That’s great!

65
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,580
Dad! Dad, I don’t believe in those things.

66
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:20,610
It’s all up to me and Lada whether we can go well together

67
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,780
You might think she’s too thin.

68
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,250
But I think she’s quite hot.

69
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,550
You’re a sweet talker.

70
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:36,480
- So, Kirk.
- Yes, Bro.

71
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:39,180
Saying that, does that mean you like her?

72
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:48,150
Well, if I were to be honest,
I more than like her. It’s love at first sight.

73
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,510
I can’t continue eating.

74
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,380
The food is too cheesy—makes me want to puke.

75
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:58,750
Lada.

76
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:01,260
Lada.

77
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,200
Lada.

78
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:07,050
Lada! Lada! Get back here right now!

79
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,550
Dad, did I say something wrong?

80
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:14,210
Let’s carry on with our meal.

81
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:26,310
Det, I’m begging you.

82
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:29,550
Lada doesn’t like Kirk. Please don’t force her into this marriage.

83
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,310
They’ll love each other after living together for a while.

84
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:36,650
Look at Wat and Mei. They’ve gone through it and are still together now.

85
00:05:37,060 --> 00:05:41,250
Just marry her off to Kirk,

86
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,950
so that she won’t be a burden to my family anymore!

87
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:49,850
If Lada is a burden to you, I can look after her myself.

88
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:52,350
We won’t bother you again.

89
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:57,080
What? What was that? Say it again!

90
00:05:58,159 --> 00:06:04,510
If looking after me and her makes you think you can do anything to us,

91
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,280
then I’ll look after her myself.

92
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:09,650
Don’t!

93
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:15,280
If you don’t stop, I’ll call the police.

94
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:22,750
Although she’s your wife, you’ve never shown her any respect!

95
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:24,210
You didn’t even sign a marriage certificate with her!

96
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:29,010
If you hurt her, it won’t be just a domestic abuse.

97
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:31,280
It’s man assaulting woman.

98
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,610
Lada!

99
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,580
You think you’re better than me?

100
00:06:39,530 --> 00:06:42,780
Then pack your things and get the hell out of here!

101
00:06:43,530 --> 00:06:47,210
Yes, I’m going to take Mum out of here now.

102
00:06:48,730 --> 00:06:53,980
Make sure you have enough cash to pay for mum’s lawsuit.

103
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:55,960
Hey!

104
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:59,350
You have no idea, don’t you?

105
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:06,250
The reason your mother always stays home and hardly goes out to see anyone, do you know why?

106
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:09,010
- No! Please stop!
- It’s because she killed someone!

107
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,180
That’s not true! Don’t listen to him.

108
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:14,280
It was an accident! I didn’t kill anyone!

109
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:17,450
Stabbing someone to death with a knife, you call that an accident?

110
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,650
- You know it too.
- Know what?

111
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:22,480
That he was trying to rape me!

112
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:25,550
I had to protect myself. It was just a self-defense!

113
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,210
You slept with that bastard.

114
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,910
And you were afraid he’d tell me.

115
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,980
That’s why you killed him.

116
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,060
Right, Mon?

117
00:07:33,159 --> 00:07:36,250
No, it’s not true! It’s not true, Lada.

118
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:37,580
Who would believe you?

119
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:41,100
All you have are your stupid words

120
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:45,250
and a knife you used to kill him which I still have it with me.

121
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:52,110
What? You’ve kept it all this time?

122
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:56,250
Why did you do that?

123
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,659
Why did you keep it? Why did you keep it?

124
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,960
How could you do this to me?

125
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,700
I wouldn’t have done it,

126
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:05,450
if it weren’t because your ungrateful child,

127
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,010
had chosen to be with the bloody Watin Group!

128
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:11,650
You think I don’t know why you don’t want to marry Kirk?

129
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,250
It’s because you love that freaking Adisorn’s daughter, isn’t it?

130
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:20,010
You can’t wait to get out of here and go live with the Watin Group, don’t you?

131
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:29,410
I’m not welcomed there. Miss Apo already knows who I am.

132
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,510
Then just listen to Dad and marry Mr. Huad’s so

133
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:40,580
Lada. Listen to me, sweetie.

134
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,100
You don’t have to do it.

135
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:52,280
You’ve done enough for me.

136
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:56,150
Whatever will be, just let it be, dear.

137
00:09:01,930 --> 00:09:03,280
Wat.
- Yes, Dad.

138
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:04,580
Call the police.

139
00:09:06,130 --> 00:09:07,410
Are you sure, Dad?

140
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:09,850
I’ll do it.

141
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:23,110
Your happiness at the cost of your mother going to jail,

142
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,410
if you think that’s worth it, then go on.

143
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:38,350
If I agree to marry him, all of this will be over, right?

144
00:10:20,330 --> 00:10:23,580
Nam! I’ve got news.

145
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:24,960
About what?

146
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,760
About Chonlada, of course.

147
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,810
How’s she? Where’s she now?

148
00:10:30,810 --> 00:10:33,580
Is she okay? Is she having any problems?

149
00:10:34,130 --> 00:10:36,380
Please calm down and listen to me.

150
00:10:37,730 --> 00:10:38,810
She’s…

151
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,110
She’s what?

152
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:43,910
Right now, she’s at Mr. Pheemdet’s house.

153
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:50,180
And is she okay? How is she doing?

154
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:54,650
She’s fine but…

155
00:10:57,860 --> 00:10:59,380
Hurry up and say it!

156
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:02,580
Promise me you’ll calm down, okay?

157
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:05,910
Calm down about what? Just say it!

158
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:08,660
Chonlada is getting married.

159
00:11:36,460 --> 00:11:40,510
Doing this won’t make anything better, do you know that?

160
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,060
Please don’t be mad at me, Nate.

161
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:48,580
Apart from Mum, you’re all I have now.

162
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:58,550
If even my best friend is mad at me, I’ll have no one else left in my life.

163
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:05,410
I told you to love yourself more. But look what you’ve done.

164
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:09,750
You let your dad marry you off with some guy you barely know.

165
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:16,880
Are you trying to ruin your own life just because you’re heartbroken?

166
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,980
I’ve always been helpless.

167
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,610
Never get to voice out my own thoughts.

168
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:27,480
That’s why I’m often used by others

169
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,610
and be rid of once they find me useless.

170
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:38,310
Whether it’s Dad, Pat, or…

171
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:41,080
I thought you said you’d heed my advice.

172
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,550
Why can’t you love yourself more, Lada?

173
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,860
I do love myself.

174
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,950
But I love my mother more.

175
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:05,180
Every decision in my life has never been easy—you also know that.

176
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,350
What if I make mistake again?

177
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:19,010
This time, it’s not just me. But Mum will be in trouble too.

178
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:56,810
May you both have lots of kids together.

179
00:13:57,530 --> 00:14:00,310
- Please always forgive each other.
- Yes, Dad.

180
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:01,950
May you two always find happiness in life.

181
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:02,760
Yes, Mum.

182
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:54,650
This one is for you.

183
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:57,910
And this one is for you, Lada.

184
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:02,610
Kirk.

185
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:03,180
Yes?

186
00:15:03,660 --> 00:15:07,910
Please take good care of her for me.

187
00:15:08,460 --> 00:15:10,110
Yes, Dad. Please don’t worry.

188
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:18,510
Lada, be a good wife to him.

189
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,280
And don’t make me wait too long to hold my grandson.

190
00:15:36,110 --> 00:15:37,010
Okay?

191
00:15:45,810 --> 00:15:47,450
What a perfect match.

192
00:15:48,730 --> 00:15:51,050
Please take care of her for me.

193
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:04,100
Of course, I'll take good care of this daughter-in-law.

194
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:23,150
Let’s take a picture together.

195
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,810
Ready?

196
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:54,310
One, two, three!

197
00:17:36,730 --> 00:17:37,850
Lada.

198
00:17:41,530 --> 00:17:44,680
You and Kirk still haven’t signed a marriage certificate yet.

199
00:17:45,810 --> 00:17:48,510
You can still change your mind, dear.

200
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:53,910
Please trust my decision, Mum.

201
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,150
[Door shutting]

202
00:18:10,530 --> 00:18:11,910
Dad said it’s time.

203
00:18:12,930 --> 00:18:15,650
But it’s not time for an evening party yet.

204
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:20,250
Dad wants Lada to sign a marriage certificate with Kirk first.

205
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,980
But I thought Dad said it’d be after the party.

206
00:18:27,730 --> 00:18:31,060
It’s a matter of benefits. That’s why it can’t wait.

207
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,110
Let me get this straight, Lada.

208
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:39,480
You’re not marrying for love. This is purely for business interest.

209
00:18:40,580 --> 00:18:42,010
Hurry up now.

210
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:03,280
Lada! There’s a commotion at the hotel.

211
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:08,150
Why do the police need to conduct a search here?

212
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:13,150
The police said they’ve found a suspicious bag in the kitchen next door.

213
00:19:18,950 --> 00:19:20,310
What happened?

214
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:50,880
My team and I will go down and pretend to inspect the bag to buy you some time.

215
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:54,810
You and Fai should hurry to room no.888. It’s Chonlada’s bridal suite.

216
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,580
Thanks a lot for helping me.

217
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:04,110
This is nothing. The hard part is how to get her out of here.

218
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,680
No matter what, I’m going to take Lada out of here with me.

219
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:10,380
I’m not gonna let her marry someone she doesn’t want to.

220
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:12,480
We’d better hurry up then.

221
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:14,410
This is the Wachara Group’s den, I don’t trust anything.

222
00:20:14,410 --> 00:20:15,680
Let’s hurry up and get it over with.

223
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,910
Why did you come up here?

224
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,010
Isn’t the suspicious bag downstairs?

225
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,550
So, what are you guys doing here?

226
00:20:58,100 --> 00:21:00,050
- Call the hotel staff.
- Yes, sir.

227
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,450
Plan B, now.

228
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:06,180
[Emergency alarm]

229
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,650
What the heck is it this time?

230
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:16,780
You two go check that side. See why the alarm goes off. Go now.

231
00:21:17,930 --> 00:21:20,110
- Wait! Hold on.
- Evacuate everyone out of the hotel.

232
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:22,210
- Let’s go.
- Wait!

233
00:21:24,110 --> 00:21:25,280
What happened?

234
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:27,210
[Commotion]

235
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:33,750
Help! Fire! Fire!

236
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:37,150
Quickly! Move!

237
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:38,810
Hurry up! Move it!

238
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,880
Sis, you go ahead. I’ll keep watch here.

239
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:50,510
Hasn’t Lom gone a bit too far?

240
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:56,850
Nam wants to steal the tiger’s cub from its den, so we must make a scene to lure the tiger out.

241
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,810
Hope Nam can rescue Lada and make it out of here.

242
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:24,380
[Lada: I’m sorry, Dad. I can’t marry him. I’m sorry.]

243
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:39,680
[Two weeks later]

244
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:18,880
I’m home!

245
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:21,950
You’re back? What have you got there?

246
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:25,010
Everything on your list, Mum.

247
00:24:25,060 --> 00:24:26,850
Whoa, that’s a lot.

248
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,850
- And also…
- Let me see.

249
00:24:29,330 --> 00:24:30,760
Mum!

250
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:31,960
What?

251
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,810
I forgot to buy your favourite noodles.

252
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:37,010
I’m sorry.

253
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:41,550
It’s all right, sweetie. Come, let’s go inside.

254
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:42,530
Not yet.

255
00:24:45,260 --> 00:24:49,280
Look, the tools kit.

256
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:51,550
I bought them just in case.

257
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:54,410
I’m going to fix the door today.

258
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:58,410
Oh, Lada.

259
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:04,010
When Wat showed us this place, he also said he’d find someone to fix the door for us.

260
00:25:04,010 --> 00:25:05,850
You don’t have to do it, dear.

261
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:09,560
That’s all right. I don’t want to trouble him.

262
00:25:10,060 --> 00:25:14,450
He already helped us a lot—renting this homestay for us before,

263
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:16,410
the wedding and even kept it a secret from Dad.

264
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:20,250
I’m so grateful I don’t know how I could repay him.

265
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:24,050
So, if there’s anything I can do, I want to do it myself.

266
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:27,350
Lada.

267
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:34,880
But this place is quite far away. I don’t think anyone can find us, right?

268
00:25:37,530 --> 00:25:39,610
Are you afraid Dad will find us?

269
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:47,910
I just want you to be able to live your life freely from now on.

270
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:51,160
It’s all right, Mum.

271
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,660
Come on, let’s go eat.

272
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:56,010
I really love spending time with you.

273
00:25:56,060 --> 00:25:57,950
So, when are you going to fix the door?

274
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,650
You have to help me too. The spare parts are so tiny.

275
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:01,950
Are you sure you can fix it?

276
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:02,960
Of course.

277
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,200
Why is the toolbox so big?

278
00:26:05,930 --> 00:26:07,850
Here you go!

279
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:11,150
Put it over here, sweetie.

280
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:19,550
Oh, it’s cooked. Right on time.

281
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,310
Give me the plate, dear.

282
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:29,710
The other day when we went to the market, I saw you keep staring at the instant noodle.

283
00:26:29,710 --> 00:26:33,450
So, I thought you must be craving for it.

284
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:38,980
Wow, it looks amazing.

285
00:26:42,730 --> 00:26:44,350
These noodles are quite good.

286
00:26:46,130 --> 00:26:50,100
That means you’re starting to open up for something plain and useless.

287
00:26:54,730 --> 00:26:56,350
It’s because you made them.

288
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:12,860
What’s wrong, sweetie?

289
00:27:14,930 --> 00:27:17,150
Something must have gotten into my eyes.

290
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:22,350
I’ll go wash first.

291
00:27:35,130 --> 00:27:36,610
Hello, Lada.

292
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:40,560
Lom?

293
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:45,210
Sorry for intruding. The door isn’t locked, so I just walked in.

294
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:51,250
End of Loneliness?

295
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:57,310
I also know someone who’s feeling lonely right now.

296
00:27:57,930 --> 00:28:01,150
Maybe she should come here so that she’ll no longer feel lonely.

297
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:04,330
How did you know I’m here?

298
00:28:06,300 --> 00:28:10,010
Actually, I must say it took me too long to figure out you’re here.

299
00:28:11,930 --> 00:28:14,200
Please answer me, how did you know I’m here?

300
00:28:19,530 --> 00:28:20,660
Careful, it’s hot.

301
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:21,960
This one looks good to

302
00:28:22,260 --> 00:28:24,210
Clear soup is mine. Blood soup is yours.

303
00:28:38,660 --> 00:28:42,060
You shared my photo to your police friends’ chat group?

304
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:48,280
Nope. I just have many police friends in almost every province.

305
00:28:50,060 --> 00:28:54,880
I’m sorry. But if I hadn’t done that, I would’ve never found out you’ve moved to live this far.

306
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:59,110
That’s why I’ve moved here—because it’s far from everyone that I know.

307
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:04,610
But for someone, it might not be far at all.

308
00:29:06,900 --> 00:29:09,510
I don’t think I have to tell you why I’ve moved all the way here.

309
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:11,850
And I don’t want anyone to know about it too.

310
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:17,950
Mr. Pheemdet already sold off his Wachara Group’s branch in Hua Hin.

311
00:29:20,660 --> 00:29:22,050
That has nothing to do with me.

312
00:29:22,860 --> 00:29:24,980
But if Mr. Pheempat comes looking for you,

313
00:29:24,980 --> 00:29:28,280
you might no longer feel safe here. Do you still think it has nothing to do with you?

314
00:29:30,330 --> 00:29:32,360
In the worst case, Mum and I can just move somewhere else.

315
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,860
Somewhere so far away no one can find us.

316
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:40,280
Are you really mad at my sister?

317
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,350
Or do you probably hate her now?

318
00:29:49,330 --> 00:29:52,880
I’m a bad person. I lied to your sister

319
00:29:54,330 --> 00:29:58,610
and even took advantage of her father’s trust in me to benefit my own family.

320
00:29:59,330 --> 00:30:01,350
But in the end, you didn’t do it though.

321
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:03,910
Nam and Uncle also don’t blame you.

322
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:06,150
They know you were used.

323
00:30:06,530 --> 00:30:08,180
You were even forced to get married.

324
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,650
That’s why Nam raided the hotel to rescue you.

325
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:16,810
Miss Apo was also at the wedding?

326
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:24,110
All this time, we’ve put our own families first.

327
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:31,480
Don’t you think it’s time to start anew and do what our hearts truly want?

328
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:35,180
Your mother killed someone!

329
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:37,110
It’s not true, dear. It was an accident!

330
00:30:37,330 --> 00:30:38,280
Don’t listen to him!

331
00:30:38,300 --> 00:30:41,410
Stabbing someone to death with a knife, you call that an accident?

332
00:30:51,730 --> 00:30:53,710
might be able to run away from the Wachara Group.

333
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:56,510
But I still have Wacharadecha blood running in me.

334
00:30:57,730 --> 00:31:01,810
You’re also well aware that Watinwanich and Wacharadecha are archenemies.

335
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:08,480
I don’t think Miss Apo and I could start anew together.

336
00:31:12,930 --> 00:31:18,180
If you keep doing this, my mum and I will have no choice but to move away.

337
00:31:22,330 --> 00:31:28,980
And please tell Miss Apo that if she really forgives me, please let me go.

338
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:32,610
Please don’t look for me, I’m begging you.

339
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:35,900
Who’s it, sweetie?

340
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:45,080
She thinks our homestay looks nice, so she just stops by for more information.

341
00:31:45,910 --> 00:31:47,580
Please feel free to look around.

342
00:31:50,100 --> 00:31:51,750
- Let’s go eat.
- Okay.

343
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:52,580
I’m starving.

344
00:31:53,310 --> 00:31:54,310
Please feel free.

345
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:56,980
Are you hungry, dear?

346
00:32:06,460 --> 00:32:08,010
You heard everything, right?

347
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:11,910
The peace ambassador has failed.

348
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,180
I’m sorry.

349
00:32:14,530 --> 00:32:15,930
You don’t have to apologise, Lom.

350
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:22,510
It’s me who has to thank you for helping me find Lada.

351
00:32:23,210 --> 00:32:26,480
Just leave the rest to me.

352
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,980
I’m out to buy noodles for you, Mum—to make up for the other day.

353
00:32:53,460 --> 00:32:55,350
I’ll hurry home when I’m done.

354
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:57,730
Okay, Mum.

355
00:33:52,260 --> 00:33:56,450
Excuse me? These sunflowers and tulips, how much are you selling them?

356
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:00,750
I’m afraid they are all taken.

357
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,980
Would you mind taking my thought of you instead?

358
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:49,800
Wait, Lada!

359
00:34:59,560 --> 00:35:01,810
I’m so glad to see you, Lada.

360
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:05,160
Since that day you’ve been gone, I couldn’t contact you at all.

361
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:10,380
You don’t answer my call or even read my text.

362
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:16,980
I just want to explain about what you heard that day.

363
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,350
You’re getting me wrong.

364
00:35:20,260 --> 00:35:21,260
The truth is…

365
00:35:21,460 --> 00:35:23,250
You already know who I am.

366
00:35:24,700 --> 00:35:26,210
Please leave me alone.

367
00:35:32,660 --> 00:35:35,480
What if I can’t leave you alone?

368
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,950
That’s none of my business.

369
00:35:55,130 --> 00:35:57,310
Because I don’t have any feelings for you anymore.

370
00:35:58,660 --> 00:35:59,850
Do you get it?

371
00:36:20,780 --> 00:36:21,750
[Car horn honking]

372
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,710
Mum.

373
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:04,300
Hm?

374
00:37:04,300 --> 00:37:07,880
Someone will come to install an online customer reception for our backend work today.

375
00:37:07,930 --> 00:37:08,730
Okay.

376
00:37:17,860 --> 00:37:19,910
Did you buy these tulips?

377
00:37:20,860 --> 00:37:24,680
No, someone from a flower shop sent them.

378
00:37:25,060 --> 00:37:28,210
Didn’t you order them?

379
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:30,910
Oh, you didn’t?

380
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:37,080
Unless I say so, please don’t accept anything delivered here next time, Mum

381
00:39:26,780 --> 00:39:30,210
[Our love will never die.]

382
00:40:12,730 --> 00:40:13,530
Here you go.

383
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:18,580
This cake is so good. Have some first.

384
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,530
Thank you, Mum.

385
00:40:20,930 --> 00:40:23,000
But I can go get it myself.

386
00:40:26,460 --> 00:40:29,550
Let me do something for you too, sweetie.

387
00:40:30,530 --> 00:40:31,330
Thank you.

388
00:40:31,660 --> 00:40:32,480
Yes, dear.

389
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:39,580
Is this our homestay webpage?

390
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:45,410
Pretty, isn’t it? I’ve only opened it for two days but there are over a hundred followers now.

391
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:49,650
That’s considered a lot for a newly opened homestay like us.

392
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:51,330
Wow, over a hundred?

393
00:40:52,260 --> 00:40:53,480
That’s a lot indeed.

394
00:40:55,730 --> 00:41:01,750
But will your dad and Pat know it’s us if they see this webpage?

395
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:07,750
They won’t. I’m not using my real name.

396
00:41:08,180 --> 00:41:13,710
I use our company name as a homestay owner and also as a payee.

397
00:41:13,710 --> 00:41:16,750
I also created a new email and got a new phone number.

398
00:41:18,580 --> 00:41:19,910
There’s absolutely no way they’d find out.

399
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:22,010
You’re so smart, my girl.

400
00:41:24,980 --> 00:41:26,450
[Message notification]

401
00:41:27,580 --> 00:41:31,680
[Hi, I’d like to book two rooms for this Saturday.]

402
00:41:32,330 --> 00:41:33,410
What’s that sound?

403
00:41:33,410 --> 00:41:37,710
Mum, we’ve just got a booking!

404
00:41:38,060 --> 00:41:38,730
Booking?

405
00:41:38,730 --> 00:41:40,330
Yes, at our homestay!

406
00:41:41,530 --> 00:41:45,250
Really? How many guests? How many rooms do they want?

407
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:48,910
But we only have two rooms decorated. Will they be okay with it?

408
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:53,610
Calm down, Mum. Let me see the booking details first.

409
00:41:56,860 --> 00:42:02,610
Our guest’s name is Miss Napa. She wants to book two rooms for this Saturday.

410
00:42:04,660 --> 00:42:08,080
This Saturday?

411
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:10,810
We have customers now!

412
00:42:20,260 --> 00:42:23,060
Geez, will she let me book a room at her homestay?

413
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,450
It’s only been operated for two days, Sis. No one would hear about it yet.

414
00:42:28,450 --> 00:42:30,880
Besides, you’re using a new account.

415
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,450
There’s no way she’d know it’s you. Don’t worry.

416
00:42:40,930 --> 00:42:44,350
Hey, she has replied.

417
00:42:44,700 --> 00:42:47,850
See? What did I just say?

418
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:49,530
Told you not to worry.

419
00:42:53,700 --> 00:42:58,810
Sorry, our homestay is fully booked at the moment.

420
00:42:58,810 --> 00:42:59,950
What?

421
00:43:02,530 --> 00:43:04,250
It’s been opened for only two days.

422
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:08,150
People hardly know about it, plus this is not during a high season.

423
00:43:08,150 --> 00:43:09,310
Are you serious?

424
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:17,530
How?

425
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:35,510
Lada, both rooms at our homestay are still available, why did you reject the booking?

426
00:43:37,530 --> 00:43:39,880
I’ll let you in on another secret.

427
00:43:39,880 --> 00:43:45,610
When Nam was young, all the friends in her class had their names ended with an ‘a’.

428
00:43:45,610 --> 00:43:51,450
So, she secretly changed her name to Napa.

429
00:43:52,730 --> 00:43:59,250
Napa? Why Napa?

430
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,880
I’ll go arrange the flowers, Mum.

431
00:44:53,010 --> 00:44:56,280
[Drone flying]

432
00:45:23,410 --> 00:45:31,810
[I miss you]

433
00:45:35,050 --> 00:45:40,110
[Forgive me]

434
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:38,480
Just wait, I’ll make you praise me for doing a great job one day.

435
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:43,210
Good, I’ll be waiting.

436
00:51:12,700 --> 00:51:14,250
One bowl of wonton soup, please.

437
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:20,880
Why did you order a wonton soup for me?

438
00:51:21,600 --> 00:51:24,080
Because you don’t eat spicy food.

439
00:53:17,060 --> 00:53:18,100
Where are you?

440
00:53:40,260 --> 00:53:42,650
Where are you?

441
00:53:45,160 --> 00:53:48,710
I’ve come too far to turn back.

442
00:53:51,730 --> 00:53:52,530
Lada.

443
00:53:53,930 --> 00:53:56,210
It’s not just about me and you anymore.

444
00:53:57,060 --> 00:54:02,050
If I turn back now, I’ll get the others into trouble too.

445
00:54:02,660 --> 00:54:04,050
I can’t do that.

446
00:54:05,500 --> 00:54:08,010
If it’s about your mother’s case,

447
00:54:09,060 --> 00:54:11,900
Mr. Pheemdet has always lied to her.

448
00:54:13,930 --> 00:54:16,710
How did you know about that?

449
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:23,110
That man who tried to hurt your mother, he’s still alive.

450
00:54:27,500 --> 00:54:28,850
What do you mean?

451
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:36,100
That day when I went to look for you at the hotel.

452
00:54:41,060 --> 00:54:42,200
Miss Apo.

453
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,680
I already know what Miss Wayo’s planning to do.

454
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:51,610
Miss Preem told me everything.

455
00:54:51,610 --> 00:54:56,180
I’m the one who told her to let everyone know that Lada is in this room.

456
00:54:56,660 --> 00:55:00,150
Miss Preem said she’s got an informant who’s close to Lada.

457
00:55:00,930 --> 00:55:02,050
It’s you.

458
00:55:02,530 --> 00:55:07,810
That’s right. And according to Miss Wayo’s plan, after the fire alarm goes off,

459
00:55:07,810 --> 00:55:11,650
I was supposed to take Lada out of the hotel to see you.

460
00:55:11,650 --> 00:55:15,780
But when I came in here, she was gone.

461
00:55:19,400 --> 00:55:21,080
Hold on, Miss Apo.

462
00:55:23,530 --> 00:55:29,210
I went to see Lada at her place yesterday and I saw her mother, Aunt Mon, crying.

463
00:55:31,700 --> 00:55:35,510
Aunt Mon kept saying that Lada has to do this because of her.

464
00:55:37,530 --> 00:55:38,330
Why?

465
00:55:39,500 --> 00:55:41,650
Aunt Mon used to commit a crime.

466
00:55:42,160 --> 00:55:46,410
Lada’s father found out and has been using it to threaten her mother.

467
00:55:47,330 --> 00:55:51,950
Lada and Aunt Mon have never lived their lives the way they want to.

468
00:55:56,200 --> 00:56:00,950
If you finally find Lada and able to make it up with her,

469
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:04,880
please look after her for me.

470
00:56:12,100 --> 00:56:17,010
I asked Lom to check if there’s anything we could do with this case.

471
00:56:18,350 --> 00:56:24,810
It turns out the man your father kept telling your mother that he was dead…

472
00:56:25,750 --> 00:56:27,780
was actually just injured.

473
00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:32,380
Your father was the one who paid for everything

474
00:56:33,550 --> 00:56:36,880
including the hush money to keep that man silent.

475
00:56:38,260 --> 00:56:43,330
This means Dad has been lying all this time just to have control over Mum?

476
00:56:48,130 --> 00:56:54,080
But you don’t have to worry. She’s free from now on.

477
00:56:55,780 --> 00:57:02,780
You can also rest assured that your father won’t be able to use this to threaten your mother again.

478
00:57:06,160 --> 00:57:13,210
Thank you. If there’s a chance, I’ll repay your kindness for helping me.

479
00:57:13,750 --> 00:57:15,710
But if you’ll excuse me.

480
00:57:23,200 --> 00:57:24,800
Please give me a chance, Lada.

481
00:57:28,900 --> 00:57:31,660
Aren’t you also sad that we’re apart like this?

482
00:58:00,860 --> 00:58:03,650
I actually wanted to give you this ring on your birthday.

483
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:10,050
But things happened and I lost the chance.

484
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:12,730
Now that we’ve met again,

485
00:58:15,300 --> 00:58:20,450
I’ll show you that from now on, no matter what happens,

486
00:58:21,660 --> 00:58:23,580
I will never be afraid.

487
00:58:25,060 --> 00:58:26,610
The only thing I’ll be afraid of

488
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:31,160
is that I might never see you again.

489
00:58:38,960 --> 00:58:43,610
I promise that from now on, I’ll love and cherish you better than before.

490
00:58:46,500 --> 00:58:48,080
Can we please get back together?

491
00:58:59,960 --> 00:59:02,910
I’m sorry, Miss Apo.

492
00:59:04,650 --> 00:59:12,350
♫Have you ever loved me? Please let me know♫

493
00:59:12,350 --> 00:59:18,910
♫If those hugs you gave me meant anything at all♫

494
00:59:18,910 --> 00:59:25,950
♫I don’t want to imagine it alone. Do you also feel the same?♫

495
00:59:25,950 --> 00:59:31,710
♫Forget about that promise and tell me honestly♫

496
00:59:31,710 --> 00:59:36,250
♫If you’ve ever loved me at all♫

497
01:00:07,730 --> 01:00:09,730
[Next Episode]
You’re no longer needed here.

498
01:00:12,900 --> 01:00:14,010
Miss Preem.

499
01:00:15,800 --> 01:00:17,010
Yes, Big Boss?

500
01:00:18,660 --> 01:00:20,110
Boss has resigned.

501
01:00:22,200 --> 01:00:25,680
What happened? Why did she quit?

502
01:00:26,000 --> 01:00:31,980
I know she rejected you but my girl isn’t someone who would sit around being miserable like this.

503
01:00:32,330 --> 01:00:34,080
I don’t know what to do anymore, Dad.

504
01:00:36,660 --> 01:00:38,050
Miss Apo.

505
01:00:40,530 --> 01:00:41,680
What are you doing here?

506
01:01:08,180 --> 01:01:13,710
♫ Since the day you came into my life, I start to realise…♫

507
01:01:13,710 --> 01:01:17,880
♫ What it’s like to be someone who matters ♫

508
01:01:17,880 --> 01:01:23,810
♫ Feeling so warm whenever I see you♫

509
01:01:23,810 --> 01:01:26,580
♫ Who often stays close to me♫

510
01:01:26,580 --> 01:01:31,480
♫ I just want you to know♫

511
01:01:31,480 --> 01:01:38,310
♫ This feeling that’s happening inside♫

512
01:01:38,310 --> 01:01:41,380
♫ I don’t want to hide it anymore♫

513
01:01:41,380 --> 01:01:45,110
♫ I guess I’ll have to tell you♫

514
01:01:45,780 --> 01:01:49,810
♫ You’re the one that change my life ♫

515
01:01:50,550 --> 01:01:54,810
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone♫

516
01:01:54,810 --> 01:02:00,150
♫ Thank you so much for making my life meaningful♫

517
01:02:00,150 --> 01:02:06,480
♫ How lucky I am to have you♫

518
01:02:10,680 --> 01:02:16,480
[Waves of Deception]
